**Abstract:**
Text of the John G. Thompson Lecture on Christian Philosophy (1992) at University of Dayton. Examines whether there exists a viable "Catholic intellectual tradition," tracing its historical development through Aquinas's synthesis of faith and reason. Argues that this synthesis has failed historically and critiques both Enlightenment rationalism and the Aristotelian conception of knowledge that underlies Catholic theology.

